Program: The Forum
Title: The Unpredictable Planet: Understanding Volcanoes and Earthquakes
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p041svq3
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 27 Jul 2016
New ideas about volcanoes, earthquakes and other geological processes that both enrich and threaten us. Jack Stewart is joined by four leading Earth scientists in the city of Yokohama at the 2016 Goldschmidt Conference - volcanologists Tamsin Mather and Michihiko Nakamura, plate tectonics expert Carl Spandler and seismologist and Nature magazine editor John VanDecar. (Photo: Mount Fuji in Japan. Credit: Getty Images) Show less